OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F362A1781532675
OL,3,C'I was more or less sat on the bomb':
OL,4,CClosest survivor of IRA blast 30 years
OL,5,Con
OL,7,FA woman believed to be the closest
OL,8,Fsurvivor to an IRA bomb which
OL,9,Fdevastated Manchester city centre has
OL,10,Fspoken of her terror of being just
OL,11,Fyards from the blast.
OL,13,FRita O'Connell was just seconds away
OL,14,Ffrom the explosion, which has been
OL,15,Fdescribed as the largest detonated on
OL,16,FUK mainland since the Second World
OL,17,FWar, injuring more than 200 people and
OL,18,Fcausing an estimated #700 million in
OL,19,Fdamage.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/8
